Some more calculations in R

P(Y=10),Y~NegBin(p=0.4,r=3) see CANVAS which has a full explanation of this.
P(Y≤8),Y~Bin(n=15,p=0.4)
dnbinom(7,3,0.4)
## [1] 0.06449725
mynbin=function(y,r,p){
  
  choose(y-1,r-1)*p^r*(1-p)^(y-r)
}

mynbin(10,3,0.4)
## [1] 0.06449725
pbinom(8,size = 15,p=0.4)
## [1] 0.9049526
